{"actual_usd":0.15577000000000002,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":169,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30647,"reply":"\"No.\" *I rest my forearms on my knees a moment, the morning light catching on the edge of my white tie while the square stays quiet around us.* \"The cross is the atoning work — that's where Christ bears sin, where He dies for us. The resurrection isn't 'just extra'; it's God's vindication of the Son and the public victory over death, the great Amen to what the cross accomplished.\"\n\n*I rub my thumb once along the worn edge of my Bible.* \"Paul doesn't split them apart. 'Christ died for our sins' and 'was raised for our justification' belong together. But if a man says the cross was only suffering and not atonement, he's cut the heart out of the gospel. Was somebody saying it that starkly, or was it a muddier version than that?\"","rolling_24h_usd":50.73348000000004,"run_id":"955c1a0c-3174-4763-ab5f-5e1d5acea190"}
